  "description": [
    "A4 THE EVENING STAR Washington D C FRIDAY g 1B3 Truman Advisers Ask Complete Revision of Immigration Act By Robert K Walsh A presidential commissions pro posals to scrap the McCarran Walter Act and overhaul the basic philosophy and major provisions of the immigration and naturaliza tion system appeared today to face a hard fight in the new Congress The commission named oy President Truman last September declared that the present law vio lates American rights harms this countrys economic strength and foreign relations endangers na tional security and is even more complicated than the previous hodgepodge of scattered statutes it was supposed to codify The McCarranWalter ACt went Into effect less than 10 days ago Congress last summer passed it over the Presidents veto It has been highly controversial from the outset More recently it drew pro tests from alarmed foreign na tions and shipping companies During the campaign last fall Presidentelect Eisenhower came out for revamping of the law Backers to Resist Move Its backers have served notice that they will resist attacks on it in the Congress convening to morrow The Presidents commission did not deal directly with the legisla tive enactment which drew its name from"
